-- Ford, China's JMC Plan to Build $300 Million Assembly Plant in Nanchang
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-18T03:11:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-18/ford-china-s-jmc-plan-to-build-300-million-assembly-plant-in-nanchang.html

          
          
             Ford Motor Co. and Jiangling Motor
Corp., the Chinese commercial vehicle maker in which the U.S.
carmaker has a 30 percent stake, are building a $300 million
assembly plant in Nanchang, China, according to a press release
from Ford today.  
          
          


  


        